name: pymodm
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "pymodm" %}
{% set version = "0.4.3" %}


package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/{{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: b9fc352dabca1c10bc9342167ab322ce2898b68a79c42e19f0baa7d5b7578ea1

build:
  number: 0
  noarch: python
  script: {{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . -vv

requirements:
  host:
    - pip
    - python >=3.6
  run:
    - pymongo <4.0,>=3.4
    - python >=3.6

test:
  imports:
    - pymodm
    - pymodm.base

about:
  home: https://pypi.org/project/pymodm/
  summary: PyMODM is a generic ODM on top of PyMongo.
  license: Apache-2.0
  license_family: Apache
  license_file: LICENSE.txt

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - marcelotrevisani
smithy_version:
No azure token. Create a token and
put it in ~/.conda-smithy/azure.token
